#DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The minority parties in Johannesburg have installed a new sheriff in the City. Thapelo Amad, from the Al Jama-ah party, has been elected as the new Johannesburg mayor. He beat former mayor Mpho Phalatse from the DA, and Funzi Ngobeni from Action SA. eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones has the story in the video above.